 ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Santorini"]]},", ",{"type":"''","value":["also"]}," ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mykonos"]]}]},"\nOften, though not always, the main town of a Greek island will have the same name as the island; thus, ",{"type":"''","value":["Naxos"]}," is the name of the main town on ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Naxos"]]},", and ",{"type":"''","value":["Paros"]}," is the name of the main town on ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Paros"]]},". Sometimes these towns also have alternate names; thus Paros town is sometimes known as ",{"type":"''","value":["Parikia."]}," In addition to these names, the main town on an island is often also referred to locally on the island as ",{"type":"''","value":["Hora"]}," (sometimes spelled ",{"type":"''","value":["Khora"]},"), which basically means \"the place\": thus \"Hora\" on ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Naxos"]]}," means Naxos town, while \"Hora\" on ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Paros"]]}," means Paros town.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Talk"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\nThe best way to get around between islands - you already guessed - is by boat. Ferry schedules can be found at ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.openseas.gr Openseas"]}," or ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.gtp.gr GTP"]},". The main difference is that openseas can do a X to ALL search, which gives you all ferries departing from island X on a certain day which can be quite handy. Unfortunately this does not work (yet?) for Piraeus.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Itineraries"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Stay safe"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["IsPartOf"],["Greece"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["outlineregion"]]},"\n\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Commons:Category:Islands of Greece"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wi